00:16:41.550 --> 00:16:42.850
I didn't change anything.

00:16:48.430 --> 00:16:49.488
What is going on?

00:16:49.488 --> 00:16:52.180
AUDIENCE: We get to see
the shape of your lens.

00:16:52.180 --> 00:16:55.320
ALEX KOLOSKOV:
Where's the subject?

00:16:55.320 --> 00:16:56.500
Where it is?

00:16:56.500 --> 00:16:58.850
If not the top of the
bottle, you probably

00:16:58.850 --> 00:17:03.220
wouldn't really know that
this is the wine, right?

00:17:03.220 --> 00:17:05.220
There is something.

00:17:05.220 --> 00:17:06.040
That's it.

00:17:06.040 --> 00:17:10.010
You see, I increased light
almost one stop, two times

00:17:10.010 --> 00:17:10.920
brighter.

00:17:10.920 --> 00:17:13.440
It didn't help, except
the top of the bottle,

00:17:13.440 --> 00:17:17.550
because the only part which is
matte is on top of the bottle,

00:17:17.550 --> 00:17:18.170
right?

00:17:18.170 --> 00:17:23.329
So making light brighter
doesn't work here,

00:17:23.329 --> 00:17:26.980
simply because it's
glossy, glossy subject.

00:17:26.980 --> 00:17:28.740
It reflects everything.

00:17:28.740 --> 00:17:30.920
It reflects our light.

00:17:30.920 --> 00:17:34.600
It's like a mirror,
right, but not flat.

00:17:34.600 --> 00:17:37.860
Tell me-- when you stand
in front of the mirror

00:17:37.860 --> 00:17:41.490
and you don't see yourself
well, what do you do?

00:17:41.490 --> 00:17:44.160
You put lots of
lights on the mirror?

00:17:44.160 --> 00:17:46.510
No, you light yourself.

00:17:46.510 --> 00:17:48.890
So here is the same thing.

00:17:48.890 --> 00:17:51.350
You cannot really
highlight the subject.

00:17:51.350 --> 00:17:54.400
You cannot put lots of
light and see something.

00:17:54.400 --> 00:17:58.090
You can only reflect
something in it.

00:17:58.090 --> 00:18:01.690
Let's see what we can reflect.

00:18:01.690 --> 00:18:02.935
Diffusers, right?

00:18:02.935 --> 00:18:04.600
You know diffusers probably.

00:18:04.600 --> 00:18:06.670
This is basically
semi-transparent,

00:18:06.670 --> 00:18:08.160
translucent anything.

00:18:08.160 --> 00:18:10.110
This is plastic, for example.

00:18:10.110 --> 00:18:14.100
So let's do something
very simple.

00:18:14.100 --> 00:18:16.080
Boom, we start seeing
something, right?

00:18:16.080 --> 00:18:21.160
We start seeing the shape of the
subject, little bit, not much.

00:18:21.160 --> 00:18:23.160
Make it a little bit brighter.

00:18:23.160 --> 00:18:25.840
So it's more like a
bottle now, right?

00:18:25.840 --> 00:18:28.050
But still not really a bottle.

00:18:28.050 --> 00:18:30.490
If you don't know that bottle--
you don't see the shape,

00:18:30.490 --> 00:18:35.830
you don't see that it's
really cylindrical.

00:18:35.830 --> 00:18:38.860
And now, as any
studio photographer,

00:18:38.860 --> 00:18:40.560
I'm going to shape the light.

00:18:40.560 --> 00:18:45.500
I am going to create the shape
of this bottle on a diffuser

00:18:45.500 --> 00:18:47.440
so it will be just reflected.

00:18:47.440 --> 00:18:50.750
So see what I will do.

00:18:50.750 --> 00:18:53.080
Just to be doing this.

00:18:53.080 --> 00:18:55.570
OK, I turn it off for a moment.

00:18:55.570 --> 00:19:04.940
I'm connecting other light, a
little bit more serious light

00:19:04.940 --> 00:19:07.860
[INAUDIBLE].

00:19:07.860 --> 00:19:11.490
But the idea is the same.

00:19:11.490 --> 00:19:15.460
And you probably already know
what I'm going to use, right?

00:19:15.460 --> 00:19:17.590
Softbox, or in this case
it's called strip box

00:19:17.590 --> 00:19:18.790
because it's narrow.

00:19:18.790 --> 00:19:20.180
But basically it's softbox.

00:19:20.180 --> 00:19:22.220
Everyone knows
what's inside, right?

00:19:22.220 --> 00:19:23.400
No?

00:19:23.400 --> 00:19:25.250
So it's a diffuser.

00:19:25.250 --> 00:19:27.150
You mount light on
this side, right?

00:19:27.150 --> 00:19:31.330
This is special ring for special
type of lighting, [INAUDIBLE]

00:19:31.330 --> 00:19:32.490
color, for example.

00:19:32.490 --> 00:19:39.450
And inside, you have this, OK?

00:19:39.450 --> 00:19:43.880
It's a glossy box covered
with kind of foil.

00:19:43.880 --> 00:19:51.500
It has some diffuser inside and
one more diffuser on this edge.

00:19:51.500 --> 00:19:57.930
So the whole idea of all this
is to produce uniform feeling

00:19:57.930 --> 00:19:59.500
of this surface.

00:19:59.500 --> 00:20:02.266
That's it.

00:20:02.266 --> 00:20:11.660
And when we mount in a light,
OK, let's see what will happen.

00:20:11.660 --> 00:20:13.290
I have a trigger.

00:20:13.290 --> 00:20:15.700
That's a very handy thing.

00:20:15.700 --> 00:20:19.480
OK, now we kind of start
seeing more, right?

00:20:19.480 --> 00:20:22.330
It's more like a bottle.

00:20:22.330 --> 00:20:26.290
But still, the shape of the
bottle is not really visible.

00:20:26.290 --> 00:20:29.440
We can guess what kind
of shape of this bottle

00:20:29.440 --> 00:20:34.200
is simply because we have
a one to one-- of course,

00:20:34.200 --> 00:20:36.920
size has changed because
it's not a flat mirror,

00:20:36.920 --> 00:20:38.570
but we have reflection
from this guy,

00:20:38.570 --> 00:20:40.260
from our diffuser [INAUDIBLE].

00:20:40.260 --> 00:20:42.590
Three [INAUDIBLE].

00:20:42.590 --> 00:20:45.560
Let's see if I will
add just the larger.

00:20:45.560 --> 00:20:49.150
This is the same
thing, larger softbox.

00:20:49.150 --> 00:20:50.511
What will happen?

00:20:50.511 --> 00:20:53.950
[CAMERA CLICKS]

00:20:53.950 --> 00:20:58.150
OK, we see more of
the bottle, much more.

00:20:58.150 --> 00:21:02.790
Now, what's the difference
between this and this

00:21:02.790 --> 00:21:04.110
besides the shape of the light?

00:21:06.810 --> 00:21:11.970
How do you know if your
subject is glossy or not

00:21:11.970 --> 00:21:13.030
on the picture?

00:21:13.030 --> 00:21:14.460
How do you know?

00:21:14.460 --> 00:21:16.892
Does this look glossy?

00:21:16.892 --> 00:21:18.350
I can actually crop
it a little bit

00:21:18.350 --> 00:21:19.820
so you see a little bit less.

00:21:23.110 --> 00:21:26.540
And this actually is a
little bit fallen inside,

00:21:26.540 --> 00:21:28.620
but not a problem.

00:21:28.620 --> 00:21:34.670
So for me it
doesn't look glossy.

00:21:34.670 --> 00:21:36.430
This looks glossy.

00:21:36.430 --> 00:21:38.310
The previous shot is
not looking glossy.

00:21:38.310 --> 00:21:41.820
However, glossy, because it
reflects something bright,

00:21:41.820 --> 00:21:45.640
we know it, but it
does not change shape.

00:21:45.640 --> 00:21:48.260
So we need to show the
shape of the bottle.

00:21:48.260 --> 00:21:50.090
It's cylindrical.

00:21:50.090 --> 00:21:52.900
Do you know when
you're drawing things

00:21:52.900 --> 00:22:00.060
how to make from a circle
to make a sphere, right?

00:22:00.060 --> 00:22:01.870
You're creating shadow, maybe.

00:22:01.870 --> 00:22:04.360
You're creating some highlights.

00:22:04.360 --> 00:22:07.760
Basically it's a
gradient, right?

00:22:07.760 --> 00:22:10.990
If it's a flat paper,
you're creating a gradient.

00:22:10.990 --> 00:22:15.910
And for us, it looks like, hey,
there is some 3D coming, right?

00:22:15.910 --> 00:22:17.990
If takes them and
creates a shape.

00:22:17.990 --> 00:22:20.490
So I'm going to create
a gradient over here,

00:22:20.490 --> 00:22:23.960
because I cannot
do it here, right?

00:22:23.960 --> 00:22:28.900
For example, when it's matte--
remember our little guy?--

00:22:28.900 --> 00:22:33.530
we have a gradient, like here.

00:22:33.530 --> 00:22:35.010
We have bright and darker areas.

00:22:35.010 --> 00:22:37.960
We see that it's a
cylinder, basically.

00:22:37.960 --> 00:22:40.360
It was not a problem,
but on the glossy stuff,

00:22:40.360 --> 00:22:44.160
you don't see that
it's cylindrical.

00:22:44.160 --> 00:22:45.240
You cannot see it.

00:22:45.240 --> 00:22:47.230
So you need to create it here.

00:22:47.230 --> 00:22:50.489
This is what I'm going to do.

00:22:50.489 --> 00:22:51.780
I'm going to create a gradient.

00:22:51.780 --> 00:22:54.070
How do we do it?

00:22:54.070 --> 00:22:59.750
If I touch diffuser with one
side of the light on the strip

00:22:59.750 --> 00:23:03.440
box, it will be brighter.

00:23:03.440 --> 00:23:05.810
It will be sharp cut off
to the brighter area,

00:23:05.810 --> 00:23:08.890
and then it will be
gradually, the brightness

00:23:08.890 --> 00:23:11.170
will follow majorly, right?

00:23:11.170 --> 00:23:13.110
So let me do this.

00:23:13.110 --> 00:23:16.950
You see how it tuned
the light a little bit?

00:23:16.950 --> 00:23:20.068
And I do the shot.

00:23:20.068 --> 00:23:21.466
[CAMERA CLICKS]

00:23:23.800 --> 00:23:32.038
OK, we can do it
even more like this.

00:23:32.038 --> 00:23:33.529
[CAMERA CLICKS]

00:23:36.020 --> 00:23:40.800
OK, gradient-- this is
where it comes to the life.

00:23:40.800 --> 00:23:42.130
Depends on how good you are.

00:23:45.990 --> 00:23:47.880
When we create a
gradient, we start

00:23:47.880 --> 00:23:53.460
seeing that, hey, that's
how gradient looked like.

00:23:53.460 --> 00:23:55.740
It's like half of the shape,
but it's tough, right?

00:23:55.740 --> 00:23:58.380
It's like same as you
would paint this bottle.

00:23:58.380 --> 00:24:02.010
Now we just need to add
another side, right?

