00:24:34.390 --> 00:24:35.920
because you're going to crop it.

00:24:35.920 --> 00:24:38.140
It's easy to crop, right?

00:24:38.140 --> 00:24:41.430
And he didn't touch the
subject, so it's fine.

00:24:41.430 --> 00:24:43.270
But you see what's happening.

00:24:43.270 --> 00:24:45.800
We start seeing the bottle, OK?

00:24:45.800 --> 00:24:47.821
It turns really
kind of simple shot.

00:24:47.821 --> 00:24:48.320
Thank you.

00:24:48.320 --> 00:24:49.730
Thank you, Kyrill.

00:24:49.730 --> 00:24:57.040
Just showing you the approach
of how we shoot still life.

00:24:57.040 --> 00:24:58.770
We examine the subject.

00:24:58.770 --> 00:25:00.419
This is a simple
one, very simple.

00:25:00.419 --> 00:25:02.710
And I didn't finish, because
if you're going to finish,

00:25:02.710 --> 00:25:04.790
we may miss some other stuff.

00:25:04.790 --> 00:25:10.170
Because, for example,
the bottom of the bottle,

00:25:10.170 --> 00:25:12.330
what makes the reflection?

00:25:12.330 --> 00:25:14.810
Do you know?

00:25:14.810 --> 00:25:17.190
Now, the bottom, you
see it's not coming,

00:25:17.190 --> 00:25:20.980
the reflection, from our
reflectors, diffusers.

00:25:20.980 --> 00:25:25.270
It's not coming all the way
to the bottom of the bottle.

00:25:25.270 --> 00:25:27.740
Exactly-- the table.

00:25:27.740 --> 00:25:32.050
So the whole process of
still life photography

00:25:32.050 --> 00:25:35.860
is understanding where
the light or where

00:25:35.860 --> 00:25:38.051
the reflection is coming from.

00:25:38.051 --> 00:25:39.300
So we just need to understand.

00:25:39.300 --> 00:25:44.080
I see so many times when
people are struggling to get,

00:25:44.080 --> 00:25:47.160
for example, edge reflection
on something like this,

00:25:47.160 --> 00:25:49.050
where to put light/
They put in light,

00:25:49.050 --> 00:25:52.020
and it's not on the edge.

00:25:52.020 --> 00:25:55.990
Again, the whole idea is to
understand what do you see,

00:25:55.990 --> 00:25:58.590
where your light is
reflecting, and where

00:25:58.590 --> 00:26:01.570
to move your light, maybe,
to get edge reflection.

00:26:01.570 --> 00:26:04.330
For example, where
now in the shape

00:26:04.330 --> 00:26:06.450
should the light for
the edge reflection

00:26:06.450 --> 00:26:10.103
be if you want to have
tiny edge on this?

00:26:10.103 --> 00:26:11.969
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]?

00:26:11.969 --> 00:26:12.760
ALEX KOLOSKOV: Top?

00:26:12.760 --> 00:26:15.350
No, no, if edge on the side.

00:26:15.350 --> 00:26:19.290
On top, it will be like this.

00:26:19.290 --> 00:26:21.050
Let's play.

00:26:21.050 --> 00:26:25.010
I really love to play with
light, holding it like this.

00:26:25.010 --> 00:26:28.910
So on top, what did you get?

00:26:28.910 --> 00:26:32.800
Of course, this surface
reflects something on top,

00:26:32.800 --> 00:26:34.820
nothing behind.

00:26:34.820 --> 00:26:36.360
And we start moving in behind.

00:26:39.270 --> 00:26:42.770
This is where it's
hitting the camera,

00:26:42.770 --> 00:26:45.050
so we need to move it
away from the comma.

00:26:45.050 --> 00:26:49.300
This is where this edge
reflection is coming from.

00:26:49.300 --> 00:26:52.240
And you see I can
even shoot like this.

00:26:52.240 --> 00:26:56.460
It will be still edge
reflection because of the angle.

00:26:56.460 --> 00:26:57.850
It's a lot of reflection.

00:26:57.850 --> 00:26:59.310
Where is it?

00:26:59.310 --> 00:27:03.180
Simple-- we just need
to understand how,

00:27:03.180 --> 00:27:05.780
based on the shape of the
subject, where it's reflecting

00:27:05.780 --> 00:27:06.900
and what it's reflecting.

00:27:10.169 --> 00:27:14.150
So this is why I love studio
still life photography.

00:27:14.150 --> 00:27:18.070
I can spend hours to
shoot complex subject.

00:27:18.070 --> 00:27:19.130
This is a simple one.

00:27:22.680 --> 00:27:27.260
When it has mix of glossy
, glass, transparent stuff,

00:27:27.260 --> 00:27:33.570
matte, the way that you
highlight it is-- it's like,

00:27:33.570 --> 00:27:36.860
I don't know, like a maze.

00:27:36.860 --> 00:27:41.650
I mean, you can do a
lot and learn a lot,

00:27:41.650 --> 00:27:44.520
while shooting this,
about the light.

00:27:44.520 --> 00:27:48.420
One more thing
just to test you--

00:27:48.420 --> 00:27:52.460
how I fix this
reflection at the bottom,

00:27:52.460 --> 00:27:55.670
how to make reflection
to go all the way

00:27:55.670 --> 00:27:57.770
to the bottom of the bottle?

